Submission Details:
1. index.php
    This is the front page of our forum, BaseCamp, where the user can login or sign up. It also 
    shows the top five most recent posts, but the user is unable to click on them unless they're 
    logged in. The login boxes now include error checking with error messages for correct email 
    and password format.
	
2. homePage.php
    This is the front page of our forum once the user is logged in. It shows the top twenty most
    recent posts from all users.
	
3. signup.php
	This is the page where the user can sign up to create an account. It asks for first name, last
    name, email, date of birth, avatar, username, password. Clicking signup will take them to the
    logged in page. The email, username, password, password confirmation, and avatar boxes now include
    error checking with error messages for correct formatting.

4. managePost.php
    This is the page to manage all of the current user's posts. They are listed in their entirety 
    with all comments from posts attached. The user can still open these posts in the post view.
	
5. createPost.php
    This is the page to create a new post. It allows for a post title, a post body, and an image.
    There is a default image set up already which can be swapped out. The title and post body
    boxes now include error checking with error messages for correct character counts, and 
    character counters for user convenience. 
	
6. viewPost.php
    This is the page to view a post in its entirety. It can be accessed by clicking on the title
    of any post. It shows the entire post, plus the comments on it, and there is a bar at the bottom
    of the page to leave a comment. Comment boxes now include error checking with error messages for correct character counts, and
    character counters for user convenience.

7. db.php
    Sets up the database to be used for this website.
    
8. logout.php
    Closes the database and ends the session.

9. db.sql 
    The creation statements for all the database tables.

10. js/eventHandlers.js
    This is the collection of all validators and handlers for the signup page input, the login input,
    the post creation input, and the comment input. It checks that all input meets the proper
    requirements. It also displays and hides errors messages when requirements are not met. The 
    character counter is also in this file which tells the user how many characters they have left for
    comments, post titles, and post bodies.

11. js/eventRegisterComment.js
    These are the event listeners for posting a comment. It creates listeners for the comment box
    character count, submit button, and input selection.

12. js/eventRegisterCreatePost.js
    These are the event listeners for creating a post. It creates listeners for the title
    character count, post body character count, submit button, and input selection.

13. js/eventRegisterLogin.js
    These are the event listeners for logging in. It creates listeners for the email input selection,
    password input selection, and submit button.

14. js/eventRegisterSignup.js
    These are the event listeners for signing up. It creates listeners for the email input, username
    input, password input, password confirmation input, avatar photo input, and submit button.

15. css/styles.css
    This includes all the styling for each page, split up by function. There are sections for the
    profile, new posts, individual preview posts, full posts, comments, all forms, and more. It
    also includes the fonts. *Has been updated to include styling for the error messages and the 
    character count.

16. fonts/
    All the fonts used in the code are stored in this folder. 

17. images/
    All images used including logo, placeholder profile images, placeholder post photos, and
    sign up page default image.

18. uploads/
    All images for the user profile pictures and the post pictures.

19. README.md
    This is the read me for the entire project with milestones.